02:14.236 --> 02:15.913
He can't kill all of us.

02:15.916 --> 02:17.722
He's right. Individually,

02:17.725 --> 02:20.010
we are weak like a single twig.

02:20.087 --> 02:23.981
But as a bundle, we form a mighty faggot.

02:26.585 --> 02:27.893
Well said.

02:27.986 --> 02:30.341
If we all stand together, Nelson's helpless.

02:30.406 --> 02:32.312
Hell, no, we won't show.

02:32.315 --> 02:34.400
Hell, no, we won't show!

02:34.408 --> 02:36.412
Hell, no, we won't show!

02:36.415 --> 02:38.383
Hell, no, I won't mow!

02:38.386 --> 02:41.062
Willy, you're fired with complete loss of pension.

02:41.065 --> 02:41.810
Damn it!

02:42.285 --> 02:45.932
You actually convinced people not to go to Nelson's party?

02:45.935 --> 02:48.140
Yep, he'll be all alone on his birthday.

02:48.156 --> 02:49.863
Oh, I wish I could see it.

02:49.866 --> 02:51.390
Boo-hoo, I'm Nelson.

02:51.396 --> 02:52.811
No one likes me.

02:52.817 --> 02:54.820
Bartholomew J. Simpson,

02:54.837 --> 02:56.762
how can you be so mean?!

02:56.766 --> 02:58.102
What are you going to do about it?

02:59.535 --> 03:00.272
Hey!

03:00.287 --> 03:02.223
I'll whack you with
the whole salad set

03:02.236 --> 03:04.411
if you don't start
thinking about others.

03:04.417 --> 03:06.173
You are going to that party.

03:06.277 --> 03:07.892
Mom, I can't go!

03:07.897 --> 03:09.090
No one else is.

03:09.096 --> 03:10.892
Well, if no one else jumped off

03:10.895 --> 03:13.980
the Empire State Building, would you not jump?

03:16.528 --> 03:17.771
Kind of...

03:17.858 --> 03:19.352
Aw, come on, Bart.

03:19.357 --> 03:21.263
The party will be fun.

03:21.276 --> 03:22.781
Nelson's not bad.

03:22.795 --> 03:25.821
All he needs is a little kindness.

03:26.047 --> 03:27.643
Ha, ha, Haaaa

03:27.648 --> 03:29.493
Lisa, you're never gonna get a husband

03:29.496 --> 03:30.940
by being sarcastic.

03:31.217 --> 03:32.661
All right, no husband.

03:32.667 --> 03:34.163
You're getting a husband!

03:34.167 --> 03:36.231
And you are going to that party.

03:36.747 --> 03:37.183
Hmm? Hmm?!

03:39.616 --> 03:41.132
Dad, don't make me go.

03:41.137 --> 03:42.172
I'll give you a back rub.

03:45.878 --> 03:48.931
Oh, your elbow's like
an angel's kiss,

03:49.156 --> 03:50.301
but you still have to go.

03:50.308 --> 03:51.032
Why?

03:51.235 --> 03:55.143
Son, we all have to do things we don't want to:

03:55.158 --> 03:57.600
like have jobs and families

03:57.607 --> 03:59.081
and responsibilities

03:59.097 --> 04:01.023
and having to be Mr. Funny all the time.

04:01.025 --> 04:03.562
You think I wouldn't rather be living nude in the forest

04:03.566 --> 04:06.831
like some ancient pagan, just dancing around

04:06.838 --> 04:08.593
playing the pan flute?!

04:08.606 --> 04:10.361
And here we are.

04:13.667 --> 04:16.983
Okay, just walk in, say "happy birthday" and get out.

04:18.166 --> 04:19.771
Whoa!

04:20.918 --> 04:22.523
This party doesn't suck.

04:22.728 --> 04:24.570
Pizza, that's a nice touch.

04:27.366 --> 04:29.753
Uh-oh, do I hear a dial tone?

04:29.756 --> 04:31.833
'Cause this party is off the hook!

04:34.105 --> 04:35.043
What up, B?

04:36.778 --> 04:37.421
Um,

04:37.868 --> 04:39.290
happy birthday,
Nelson.

04:40.225 --> 04:42.732
Uh, I know it seems a little quiet.

04:42.737 --> 04:44.590
Must be a lot of traffic today.

04:44.596 --> 04:46.260
Is Highway 88 backed up?

04:46.286 --> 04:48.340
Oh, yeah, it's a parking lot out there.

04:48.348 --> 04:50.813
Of course, that explains everything.

04:50.817 --> 04:52.220
Stupid Highway 88!

04:52.278 --> 04:54.170
Huh?

04:58.876 --> 04:59.841
Whoa!

04:59.848 --> 05:02.253
Hi, kids, my spidey sense is tingling.

05:02.255 --> 05:05.381
Tingling because it's a certain someone's birthday.

05:06.756 --> 05:07.671
Yeah!

05:10.266 --> 05:12.131
Uh, where are all the kids?

05:12.135 --> 05:12.822
They're coming!

05:12.826 --> 05:13.552
They are!

05:14.496 --> 05:16.053
I love you, Spidey!

05:16.148 --> 05:18.932
Uh, listen, I only got ten minutes of material.

05:18.935 --> 05:21.021
Maybe I should come back a little later.

05:21.065 --> 05:21.871
Don't go.

05:21.887 --> 05:23.470
My party peeps are en route,

05:23.476 --> 05:24.562
I swear!

05:28.087 --> 05:29.322
Nelson, nobody's coming.

05:29.836 --> 05:31.813
But how could nobody come?

05:31.877 --> 05:33.380
I ordered them to.

05:33.388 --> 05:35.173
Well, that's the thing.

05:35.317 --> 05:38.691
Sometimes you can be kind of a jerk.

05:38.768 --> 05:40.290
True...

05:40.517 --> 05:43.540
but I thought I had some friends.

05:44.296 --> 05:47.102
Maybe you can have fun with just me.

05:47.177 --> 05:48.032
Okay.

05:48.405 --> 05:49.173
Why not?

05:49.178 --> 05:51.373
Stop having fun, kids.

05:51.375 --> 05:52.993
I'm Dr. Octopus

05:52.998 --> 05:54.820
from Marvel Comics' Spiderman.

05:54.825 --> 05:56.270
I'm inventing a ray

05:56.275 --> 05:57.971
that turns birthday presents

05:57.978 --> 05:59.093
into homework.

05:59.095 --> 06:00.390
Yah!

06:00.405 --> 06:01.060
Come on, Bart.

06:01.104 --> 06:02.321
Let's knock him down.

06:13.733 --> 06:15.218
Wait, I have an idea.

06:22.041 --> 06:23.479
Look at our kids,

06:23.479 --> 06:24.890
playing like champs.

06:24.896 --> 06:27.430
Yeah. How'd you afford this kickass party?

06:27.435 --> 06:29.882
Carnival ride hit me on the head.

06:30.216 --> 06:31.010
Hmm....

06:31.178 --> 06:34.472
So how was Nelson's party?

06:34.516 --> 06:35.323
Not bad.

06:35.336 --> 06:37.763
We had pizza, cake and then sang songs

06:37.767 --> 06:38.953
with Nelson's grandma.

06:38.955 --> 06:41.092
But it was a one-time thing,

06:41.098 --> 06:43.143
and now I'll never see him again.

06:44.258 --> 06:45.190
Hey!

06:45.196 --> 06:46.921
It's my birthday bud!

06:49.205 --> 06:50.710
Yeah, yeah, it was,

06:50.718 --> 06:52.030
uh, super fun.

06:52.035 --> 06:52.952
Good times.

06:52.955 --> 06:53.690
Hey, Ralph,

06:53.698 --> 06:55.803
