14:49.937 --> 14:52.652
Well ere's something in my eye, too.

14:56.345 --> 14:57.982
Ma, what happened to the curtains?

14:58.288 --> 15:01.053
I made 'emo a dress
for karaoke singing.

15:01.605 --> 15:03.043
Hey Bart, do you want some ice cream?

15:03.246 --> 15:05.701
I just hit a major marshmallow vein.

15:05.807 --> 15:08.922
Oh! I think it goes
all the way to the bottom.

15:09.025 --> 15:11.153
- No, thanks.
- What's wrong?

15:11.557 --> 15:14.371
Me and Nelson were best friends,
and now I think he's gonna kill me!

15:14.377 --> 15:15.543
Bully problem, eh?

15:15.847 --> 15:18.430
You know what they say
all bullies are cowards.

15:18.635 --> 15:22.170
It's not true-- they're brave,
'cause they're strong.

15:28.698 --> 15:30.483
Bart, we need to talk.

15:32.705 --> 15:35.530
I feel so bad about
freaking out on you.

15:35.637 --> 15:37.702
It'll never happen again, I swear.

15:38.007 --> 15:40.341
Um... okay.

15:40.647 --> 15:43.200
Best friends?
Forever?

15:43.508 --> 15:44.323
No!

15:44.327 --> 15:45.330
I can't do it.

15:45.335 --> 15:47.472
You're a nut bar, a whack job!

15:47.475 --> 15:48.481
A kooka-dooka!

15:48.488 --> 15:50.502
Please, just leave me alone.

15:50.658 --> 15:52.803
- Best not to get involved.
- Agreed.

15:55.807 --> 15:58.343
Looks like you've
made your choice.

15:58.646 --> 16:01.400
Make sure your affairs
are in order.

16:01.405 --> 16:02.673
I've set up a trust.

16:02.678 --> 16:04.683
It bypasses the inheritance tax.

16:04.808 --> 16:07.253
Only till 2008.
Look into it!

16:10.985 --> 16:12.751
Oh, Greystash...

16:13.957 --> 16:15.843
Greystash!

16:15.846 --> 16:16.842
Oh, hello, Lisa.

16:16.985 --> 16:18.802
Come on, Dad, read
the last chapter.

16:18.905 --> 16:20.671
Everyone says there's a big surprise.

16:20.707 --> 16:23.901
I bet Angelica discovers
that she's a wizard.

16:25.205 --> 16:28.691
How would you feel if something
bad happened to Greystash?

16:28.796 --> 16:31.003
It would be the day my childhood ended.

16:31.507 --> 16:32.852
Come on, read, read!

16:35.206 --> 16:39.123
"Angelica was trapped in the
Suffoclock of Sandy Doom..."

16:39.188 --> 16:42.503
Time to choose, Greystash.
If you save Angelica,

16:42.555 --> 16:44.001
you die!

16:45.056 --> 16:45.883
Why are you stopping?

16:45.906 --> 16:47.701
We're almost at the happy ending.

16:49.006 --> 16:51.053
No book is gonna make
my daughter sad.

16:51.357 --> 16:54.951
Time to do what I do best.
Lie to a child!

16:55.156 --> 16:58.241
"Greystash looked Krubb
right in the eye and said..."

16:59.895 --> 17:02.303
Mustache power:
activate!

17:17.435 --> 17:20.853
Oh, man, I can't believe
you beat me, but you did.

17:21.255 --> 17:24.381
I somehow escaped
from the hourglass!

17:26.366 --> 17:28.780
And now, to go on living!

17:35.056 --> 17:36.620
The end.

17:37.908 --> 17:39.620
Is that really how it ends?

17:39.685 --> 17:41.820
What happened to
the Merlinical Council?

17:42.857 --> 17:45.661
They went to Star Wars Land
and fought star wars.

17:45.708 --> 17:48.582
Dad, you can read to me anytime.

17:49.608 --> 17:52.351
Now Lisa won't know
about death till it strikes

17:52.406 --> 17:53.950
someone close to her.

18:04.408 --> 18:05.791
Dad's ending is better.

18:05.966 --> 18:09.503
Okay, field-trippers, welcome to
the Springfield Tide Pools,

18:09.556 --> 18:11.822
nature's most fecund ecosystem.

18:12.026 --> 18:14.202
Who will spot
the playful abalone?

18:14.205 --> 18:15.743
The mighty winkle?

18:16.046 --> 18:18.083
I think it might be you, Sherri.

18:18.958 --> 18:20.983
Now, remember,
these pools can be dangerous,

18:20.997 --> 18:22.503
so everyone pick a buddy.

18:23.658 --> 18:25.030
Bart's my buddy.

18:25.707 --> 18:26.563
Good boy, Nelson.

18:27.007 --> 18:28.400
Squeeze him extra tight for safety.

18:31.906 --> 18:33.753
We sure are far from
the rest of 'em.

18:34.438 --> 18:35.951
Funny how that happened, huh?

18:36.645 --> 18:37.322
Come with me.

18:39.808 --> 18:41.280
Nelson, please don't kill me.

18:41.376 --> 18:43.432
Remember when we made
fun of Cinco de Mayo?

18:43.435 --> 18:44.752
I called it "Stinko de Mayo."

18:44.855 --> 18:45.993
We laughed so hard.

18:46.806 --> 18:47.602
Bart...

18:48.696 --> 18:51.472
you are a bad friend.

18:52.406 --> 18:53.602
S-Say again?

18:53.606 --> 18:55.372
You never liked me for me.

18:55.407 --> 18:58.293
You liked that I protected
you and gave you a vest

18:58.297 --> 19:00.080
and stole milk boxes for you.

19:00.308 --> 19:03.082
I hate milk!
It comes from cow wangs!

19:03.406 --> 19:04.662
There you go again.

19:04.665 --> 19:06.862
You act all nice,
and then you go crazy.

19:06.866 --> 19:09.102
Well, maybe I get jealous.

19:09.307 --> 19:10.540
But it's just because...

19:11.305 --> 19:13.893
I never had a best friend before.

19:17.408 --> 19:20.113
Nelson, was the water
always up to our necks?

19:21.805 --> 19:22.682
Nelson?

19:23.487 --> 19:24.700
Help! Help!

19:24.948 --> 19:27.080
- Put this on.
- Where did you get it?

19:27.097 --> 19:28.131
Dude gave it to me.

19:54.056 --> 19:54.982
Man lips!

19:55.287 --> 19:59.530
Skinner loves Bart!
Skinner loves Bart!

19:59.587 --> 20:02.141
Shut up! I'm just giving him CPR,

20:02.198 --> 20:03.381
the kiss of life.

20:03.407 --> 20:05.372
And if anyone loves Bart, it's Nelson.

20:05.377 --> 20:06.183
Where is Nelson?

20:06.185 --> 20:08.401
I'm sorry, Nelson
never woke up.

20:08.406 --> 20:10.503
- What?!
- Never woke up, because...

20:10.538 --> 20:12.723
he never passed out
he's right over there.

20:16.145 --> 20:17.503
Hey, thanks for saving me, man.

20:17.707 --> 20:20.451
Course I saved you
you're my field trip buddy.

20:20.855 --> 20:23.233
- And nothing else.
- You mean...?

20:23.356 --> 20:25.881
Exactly.
You're barf to me now.

20:37.358 --> 20:38.953
Oh, Nelson...

20:39.006 --> 20:41.752
I'll never forget that week
we were best friends.

20:51.557 --> 20:53.203
I touched your heart!

21:06.525 --> 21:10.632
Greystash! Greystash!

21:11.207 --> 21:13.561
Gee, you're really upset
about this Greystash thing.

21:13.597 --> 21:14.872
Don't say his name.

21:15.277 --> 21:17.403
In your mouth,
it sounds like dirt!

21:17.456 --> 21:19.050
Homer, it's just a book.

21:19.106 --> 21:22.281
No man should outlive
his fictional wizard.

21:22.387 --> 21:23.483
No man!

